result.execSummary:
The defendant Robert S Cuellar was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Issue of Worthless Checks(<=$2500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.24(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: $100 fine plus costs. (fine and costs have been paid in full)

records.addlTxt: Defendant Robert S Cuellar in court.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Minute sheet. Court reviews events in file. Defendant indicates he is accepting the State's offer.   State gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters guilty plea.  Defendant stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds plea made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts plea, and finds guilty. Bond is no longer in effect.
Defendant was fingerprinted 6/29/15 by jail staff.
To be fingerprinted and photographed before leaving the Justice Center. Not to write any checks while matter is pending.

Defendant Robert S Cuellar in court.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews charge(s), max. penalties, right to counsel.   Defendant wants to try to resolve matter with DA, waives right to Counsel.  Court questions Defendant, finds defendant competent to proceed, finds waiver made freely and voluntarily, accepts waiver.  Defendant to make appointment with DA.  Bond set.  Status conference scheduled for August 24, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Robert S Cuellar appears by phone.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant indicates he couldn't find anyone to work for him today. Court reschedules matter to next Monday, 6/29/15 at 10:00 am.  Initial appearance scheduled for June 29, 2015 at 10:00 am.
